concepts:
Foreign direct investment consists of: - contributions to equity (equity /charter, reserve and other capital) actually made by the foreign co-owners of the enterprise; 
- financial leasing, which is a type of long-term lease in which the lessor transfers the property to the lessee as a leased asset for a certain fee, for a certain period and under certain conditions for temporary possession and use;  reinvested profits, consisting of a portion of profits owned by a direct investor, directed to expand his participation in the company's activities;
- other investments that cover operations to attract borrowed funds – loans and borrowings received from non–residents, trade loans/advances - trade payables to non-residents for the import of goods and services, as well as advances received from non-residents for the future supply of inventories, works and services (prepayment for the export of goods and services), other accounts payable to non–residents - obligations for taxes, salaries, dividends and deductions, as well as other obligations.
